If you are in Rotterdam, come by for the second official exhibition in our XP gallery View in browser 

Extra Practice goes back into gallery mode on 30/8, come visit Emma's solo show!

Dear friend,

This is a bonus e-mail! One of the reasons we moved to a bigger location was so that we could organise more events, such as art shows. We already demonstrated at The 4 Openings that we can transform our studio into an exhibition space in the blink of an eye... So the last weekend of August we are doing it again, this time to showcase a selection of XP's own Emma Verhoeven's installations and digital works.

Opening drinks
Friday 30 Aug
18:00 21:00

Visiting hours
Saturday 31 Aug Wednesday 4 Sept
every day between 11:00 17:00 

It's been a while since Emma has taken herself seriously as an artist... When you ask her about her work, she will often start mumbling, look down at the floor, and try to change the subject. But no longer! Since most of Emma's work is about self-improvement and mental health, she has decided to improve her professional artist-self once and for all, and treat her work with the love and spotlights they deserve. Just like many of the projects on show, making this exhibition happen is a form of therapy for Emma. From large and tiny media installations and classic VR trips to existential video-collages and never-before-seen sketches, it's time to dig deep into the archive of her soul and get it all out before figuring out where to go next. Will you join her on this therapeutic journey?

Come celebrate this self-helpful breakthrough at the opening on August 30 or visit our gallery between Saturday 31st and Wednesday 4th! 

Love,

The XP curators 
Extra Practice
